The paper deals with trajectory optimization for mobile manipulators, which is a topic that falls under the robotics (RO) sub-category. The paper also involves optimization techniques such as quadratic programming (QP) and Alternating Direction Method of Multipliers (ADMM), which are commonly used in the systems and control (SY) sub-category. The paper also mentions the use of parallel computing, which falls under the machine learning (LG) sub-category. Additionally, the paper involves collision avoidance and path planning, which are topics that fall under computer vision (CV) and artificial intelligence (AI) sub-categories.
